  "body": "When installing truffle globally, truffle installation is completed but doesn't actually get installed in the folder with global packages.\r\n\r\n```\r\n/home/ec2-user/.nvm/versions/node/v6.14.3/lib/node_modules/node/bin/truffle -> /home/ec2-user/.nvm/versions/node/v6.14.3/lib/node_modules/node/lib/node_modules/truffle/build/cli.bundled.js\r\n+ truffle@4.1.11\r\nupdated 1 package in 2.46s\r\n```\r\n\r\nFollowing which 'truffle init' always returns command not found error. I tried this locally or on EC2 instance with the same result. Node and NPM were updated to the latest version.\r\n\r\nWhen I throw in sudo, it does the same thing locally, in cloud it doesn't even install and it gives me UNABLE_TO_GET_ISSUER_CERT_LOCALLY . I can install it locally (which is often recommended as a solution), and this works but when I try to \"init\" it, truffle complains that the folder is not empty.\r\n\r\nAnybody has some idea how to get this resolved?",
